1
00:00:30,117 --> 00:00:32,316
[church bell tolling]

2
00:00:49,115 --> 00:00:50,778
[metal creaking]

3
00:00:53,914 --> 00:00:56,283
[♪ slow suspenseful
music playing]

4
00:01:01,819 --> 00:01:03,679
[pulley creaking]

5
00:01:05,153 --> 00:01:07,316
[indistinct conversation
in Italian]

6
00:01:22,946 --> 00:01:25,217
[man] I told you
not to look for me.

7
00:01:26,919 --> 00:01:28,481
[man 2] Please, Father.

8
00:01:35,720 --> 00:01:37,712
[object rustling]

9
00:01:41,645 --> 00:01:43,514
[man] That's all I have.

10
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:47,646
The only proof
of what they've done.

11
00:01:48,688 --> 00:01:50,277
But she looks so...

12
00:01:50,412 --> 00:01:51,415
[man] Human.

13
00:01:55,055 --> 00:01:57,415
But don't let
yourself be fooled.

14
00:01:59,945 --> 00:02:03,250
She wasn't
conceived naturally.

15
00:02:03,386 --> 00:02:06,019
[♪ solemn choral
music playing]

16
00:02:11,547 --> 00:02:13,316
<i>They found a volunteer.</i>

17
00:02:15,886 --> 00:02:17,481
<i>Someone devoted.</i>

18
00:02:20,185 --> 00:02:21,345
[man 2] <i>But how did they...</i>

19
00:02:21,480 --> 00:02:22,613
[man] <i>No, please.</i>

20
00:02:23,446 --> 00:02:25,151
<i>I can't, uh...</i>

21
00:02:27,250 --> 00:02:29,014
<i>I can't talk about that.</i>

22
00:02:29,150 --> 00:02:31,349
[breath shuddering]

23
00:02:35,183 --> 00:02:37,547
[breathing quickening]

24
00:02:41,413 --> 00:02:43,152
[gasping in fear]

25
00:02:43,921 --> 00:02:46,118
[♪ sinister music playing]

26
00:02:49,678 --> 00:02:51,349
What I can tell you...

27
00:02:53,013 --> 00:02:55,819
is that the pregnancy
happened quickly.

28
00:02:55,955 --> 00:02:58,151
[♪ sinister music continues]

29
00:03:02,085 --> 00:03:05,019
She'll be in her teens now.

30
00:03:05,154 --> 00:03:07,514
They're just waiting
until she's old enough.

31
00:03:08,853 --> 00:03:10,184
Old enough for what?

32
00:03:12,645 --> 00:03:13,652
Old enough for what?

33
00:03:13,788 --> 00:03:15,547
[man] Now, please. [sighs]

34
00:03:19,313 --> 00:03:20,481
[inhales]

35
00:03:23,546 --> 00:03:26,185
I can't do this anymore.

36
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:29,518
[woman sobbing]
<i>I can't do this anymore.</i>

37
00:03:29,653 --> 00:03:31,415
<i>I can't.</i>

38
00:03:31,551 --> 00:03:35,151
But please
don't let it touch me again.

39
00:03:35,287 --> 00:03:38,151
- [woman shuddering]
- [raspy breathing]

40
00:03:42,446 --> 00:03:45,481
- [raspy breathing intensifies]
- [♪ tense music building]

41
00:03:48,446 --> 00:03:49,547
[music stops]

42
00:03:50,916 --> 00:03:52,118
Father?

43
00:03:53,919 --> 00:03:55,182
[breathing heavily]

44
00:03:55,318 --> 00:03:57,481
[♪ foreboding music playing]

45
00:03:59,621 --> 00:04:00,613
Father Harris?

46
00:04:02,751 --> 00:04:03,745
Father?

47
00:04:08,879 --> 00:04:10,614
Hiding won't
absolve your sins.

48
00:04:11,116 --> 00:04:13,415
[pulley creaking]

49
00:04:14,484 --> 00:04:16,679
You think I want
to be forgiven? [scoffs]

50
00:04:22,047 --> 00:04:25,416
- [creaking continues]
- [worker speaking Italian]

51
00:04:25,552 --> 00:04:28,250
I don't want to be forgiven,
Father Brennan.

52
00:04:29,647 --> 00:04:32,118
I just want it all to be over.

53
00:04:33,820 --> 00:04:35,284
You'll understand...

54
00:04:36,087 --> 00:04:37,482
- soon enough.
- [rope creaks]

55
00:04:37,618 --> 00:04:39,613
- [worker shouts in panic]
- [metal clatters]

56
00:04:40,688 --> 00:04:43,815
[eerie raspy breathing]

57
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:46,511
[soft clinking]

58
00:04:46,646 --> 00:04:49,019
[raspy breathing continues]

59
00:05:02,085 --> 00:05:04,349
[♪ eerie music playing]

60
00:05:16,085 --> 00:05:17,782
[♪ music swells]

61
00:05:17,918 --> 00:05:18,947
[music stops]

62
00:05:19,082 --> 00:05:20,547
[grunting]

63
00:05:25,184 --> 00:05:27,019
Father, are you all right?

64
00:05:31,686 --> 00:05:33,085
I'm fine.

65
00:05:36,688 --> 00:05:38,646
[glass shards crunching]

66
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:48,614
Father.

67
00:05:48,749 --> 00:05:50,745
[♪ soft suspenseful
music playing]

68
00:05:57,215 --> 00:05:59,250
[breath trembling]

69
00:06:00,552 --> 00:06:03,250
[♪ pleasant classical
music playing]

70
00:06:29,148 --> 00:06:31,679
[♪ pleasant classical music
continues playing]

71
00:06:49,513 --> 00:06:51,250
[indistinct chatter]

72
00:06:58,050 --> 00:06:59,316
[music fades out]

73
00:07:02,453 --> 00:07:03,819
[announcer on PA]
<i>Il volo sette quattro due,</i>

74
00:07:03,954 --> 00:07:05,318
<i>in arrivo da Milano Linate,</i>

75
00:07:05,453 --> 00:07:08,543
<i>arrivera con quindici minuti
di ritardo.</i>

76
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:09,849
- Margaret Daino?
- Yes.

77
00:07:09,984 --> 00:07:11,019
- Hi.
- Hi.

78
00:07:11,155 --> 00:07:12,449
- I'm Father Gabriel.
- Hello. [chuckles]

79
00:07:12,584 --> 00:07:14,252
Cardinal Lawrence sent me
to fetch you.

80
00:07:14,388 --> 00:07:16,476
- Oh, sure. Thank you.
- Let me help you with that.

81
00:07:16,612 --> 00:07:18,579
He's in the car outside.

82
00:07:18,714 --> 00:07:20,249
I have heard
so much about you.

83
00:07:20,385 --> 00:07:22,151
I feel like
I already know you.

84
00:07:22,885 --> 00:07:24,344
Oh. [chuckles]

85
00:07:24,479 --> 00:07:25,648
[Lawrence] Maggie!

86
00:07:25,783 --> 00:07:29,417
- I'm so happy to see you.
- Oh, me too. [gasps]

87
00:07:29,552 --> 00:07:31,886
Oh, it's so beautiful here.
It's like a dream.

88
00:07:32,022 --> 00:07:33,951
Well, wait till you see
the actual city.

89
00:07:34,086 --> 00:07:35,584
- [laughing]
- Look at you.

90
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:37,810
It hasn't been a year,
and somehow,
you've found a way

91
00:07:37,946 --> 00:07:39,685
- to grow up even more.
- [chuckles]

92
00:07:39,821 --> 00:07:40,749
Is that
all you've got?

93
00:07:40,884 --> 00:07:41,819
That's it.

94
00:07:41,955 --> 00:07:43,886
- Well, my word. Come on.
- [laughing]

95
00:07:44,022 --> 00:07:45,712
I'll show you
to your new home.

96
00:07:47,513 --> 00:07:50,481
[<i>♪ Some Velvet Morning</i>
by Nancy Sinatra
& Lee Hazlewood plays]

97
00:08:12,851 --> 00:08:14,613
[horns honking]

98
00:08:16,150 --> 00:08:18,419
So, what do you think?

99
00:08:18,554 --> 00:08:19,713
It's wild.

100
00:08:20,349 --> 00:08:22,177
Everything's so different.

101
00:08:22,313 --> 00:08:24,015
Every street that we pass,
there's something to look at.

102
00:08:24,150 --> 00:08:25,919
I just wanna explore.

103
00:08:26,054 --> 00:08:27,252
[Lawrence]
Isn't it beautiful?

104
00:08:27,387 --> 00:08:30,415
What better place
for you to be taking the veil?

105
00:08:32,055 --> 00:08:34,477
It's wonderful
to see you, Maggie.

106
00:08:34,613 --> 00:08:35,777
Even when you were little,

107
00:08:35,913 --> 00:08:38,679
I knew you were destined
for great things.

108
00:08:40,019 --> 00:08:41,583
- [window thuds]
- [gasps]

109
00:08:41,718 --> 00:08:44,481
[Lawrence] See if you can get
around them, Damiano.

110
00:08:44,950 --> 00:08:46,520
[car roof thuds]

111
00:08:46,655 --> 00:08:48,844
[Lawrence] These protests
have picked up recently,
I'm afraid.

112
00:08:48,979 --> 00:08:50,851
[Margaret]
What are they protesting?

113
00:08:50,986 --> 00:08:51,919
[Lawrence] For the workers,

114
00:08:52,055 --> 00:08:53,511
it's about conditions
and wages.

115
00:08:53,646 --> 00:08:56,115
But for the students, well,

116
00:08:56,251 --> 00:08:58,749
it's a rejection
of authority,

117
00:08:58,884 --> 00:09:00,417
even the church.

118
00:09:01,353 --> 00:09:04,977
The world is changing,
Maggie, very fast.

119
00:09:05,112 --> 00:09:06,844
The younger generation
no longer turn to us

120
00:09:06,980 --> 00:09:08,978
- for guidance, I'm afraid.
- [man] Ooh!

121
00:09:09,113 --> 00:09:11,785
[Lawrence] But it's
a challenge we've embraced.

122
00:09:11,921 --> 00:09:13,084
Perhaps you'll play your part

123
00:09:13,219 --> 00:09:15,250
and help
earn back their trust.

124
00:09:16,917 --> 00:09:18,184
I'll try.

125
00:09:19,919 --> 00:09:21,710
<i>Come la treccia!</i>

126
00:09:21,845 --> 00:09:23,783
[♪ choral music playing]

127
00:09:23,919 --> 00:09:25,514
[indistinct chatter]

128
00:09:41,851 --> 00:09:42,849
[door opens]

129
00:09:42,985 --> 00:09:44,549
[footsteps approaching]

130
00:09:44,684 --> 00:09:48,084
<i>Tu devi essere
la nostra bella Americana.</i>

131
00:09:48,220 --> 00:09:49,584
[Lawrence]
This is Sister Silva,

132
00:09:49,719 --> 00:09:50,678
the Abbess.

133
00:09:50,814 --> 00:09:52,711
And she'll take
good care of you.

134
00:09:52,847 --> 00:09:54,850
- Hello.
- [Silva] <i>Bellissima.</i>

135
00:09:54,985 --> 00:09:56,718
Welcome to our family.

136
00:09:56,854 --> 00:09:58,914
Oh. [chuckles] Thank you.

137
00:09:59,049 --> 00:10:00,250
Ooh. [chuckles]

138
00:10:02,754 --> 00:10:04,613
Come. Come with me.

139
00:10:05,579 --> 00:10:07,317
Let me give you a tour.

140
00:10:08,187 --> 00:10:10,646
We're so happy
to have you here.

141
00:10:15,917 --> 00:10:17,118
This way.

142
00:10:17,820 --> 00:10:18,980
We take care of girls.

143
00:10:19,115 --> 00:10:20,683
Girls only.

144
00:10:20,819 --> 00:10:22,718
A total of 62.

145
00:10:22,854 --> 00:10:25,947
Babies to 18 years of age.

146
00:10:26,083 --> 00:10:27,514
Come this way.

147
00:10:29,149 --> 00:10:30,743
<i>Buongiorno.</i>

148
00:10:30,878 --> 00:10:32,083
[girls] <i>Buongiorno.</i> Hello.

149
00:10:32,218 --> 00:10:34,310
[Margaret laughs] <i>Buongiorno.</i>

150
00:10:34,445 --> 00:10:35,381
[babies crying]

151
00:10:35,517 --> 00:10:37,216
The state has
contracted with us

152
00:10:37,351 --> 00:10:39,082
to take in
many unmarried women

153
00:10:39,217 --> 00:10:40,786
who are about to give birth.

154
00:10:40,921 --> 00:10:42,543
We have
our birthing facilities

155
00:10:42,679 --> 00:10:44,349
here in the hospital wing.

156
00:10:47,587 --> 00:10:49,286
Come, come.

157
00:10:49,422 --> 00:10:53,148
Our doctor will likely deliver
this baby within the week.

158
00:10:53,284 --> 00:10:55,885
<i>- Ciao, Lanoma.
- Salve.</i>

159
00:10:56,020 --> 00:10:58,449
<i>- Come stai?
- Bene.</i>

160
00:10:58,584 --> 00:11:01,381
[Silva] <i>Tranquilla.
Tutto va bene.</i>

161
00:11:01,517 --> 00:11:04,547
<i>- Pazienza, hmm?</i>
- [woman crying]

162
00:11:08,478 --> 00:11:09,547
<i>Andiamo.</i>

163
00:11:14,752 --> 00:11:16,613
[humming softly]

164
00:11:18,379 --> 00:11:20,283
Sister Anjelica.

165
00:11:23,121 --> 00:11:26,613
This is Margaret Daino
from America.

166
00:11:28,821 --> 00:11:30,448
[♪ cryptic music plays]

167
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:36,710
<i>She grew up here.</i>

168
00:11:36,845 --> 00:11:39,750
<i>Abandoned on our front steps,</i>

169
00:11:39,885 --> 00:11:40,817
<i>and very ill.</i>

170
00:11:40,952 --> 00:11:43,779
But she's very devoted

171
00:11:43,914 --> 00:11:47,384
and she keeps
all the children smiling.

172
00:11:47,519 --> 00:11:49,419
- And they all seem very happy.
- [girls shouting]

173
00:11:49,554 --> 00:11:51,517
[girl screaming]

174
00:11:51,652 --> 00:11:52,777
<i>Scusi.</i>

175
00:11:52,913 --> 00:11:55,452
I should see
what the trouble is.

176
00:11:55,587 --> 00:11:56,580
Of course.

177
00:11:58,188 --> 00:12:00,178
[nun] <i>Via dal
cancello faccello.</i>

178
00:12:00,314 --> 00:12:03,183
[girl whispering] <i>La tua
suora e sempre gentilissima.</i>

179
00:12:03,318 --> 00:12:05,247
[♪ girls singing in classroom]

180
00:12:05,382 --> 00:12:07,580
[girl continues whispering]

181
00:12:24,083 --> 00:12:27,679
[♪ girl in room singing]
<i>♪ Ave Maria ♪</i>

182
00:12:28,954 --> 00:12:32,316
<i>♪ Gratia plena ♪</i>

183
00:12:32,950 --> 00:12:34,948
[door creaking]

184
00:12:35,083 --> 00:12:36,116
[soft scratching]

185
00:12:36,251 --> 00:12:39,349
<i>♪ Dominus tecum ♪</i>

186
00:12:40,713 --> 00:12:45,019
<i>♪ Sancta Maria ♪</i>

187
00:12:45,987 --> 00:12:49,316
<i>♪ Mater Dei ♪</i>

188
00:12:49,916 --> 00:12:52,712
Amen.

189
00:12:54,412 --> 00:12:55,646
Hail Mary.

190
00:13:04,378 --> 00:13:05,610
Um...

191
00:13:05,746 --> 00:13:07,613
<i>Ave Maria</i> is my favorite, too.

192
00:13:09,787 --> 00:13:12,019
<i>Il mio preferito.</i>

193
00:13:15,217 --> 00:13:17,646
[chuckles] What's your name?

194
00:13:18,885 --> 00:13:20,382
<i>Come ti chiami?</i>

195
00:13:25,786 --> 00:13:27,118
I'm Margaret.

196
00:13:28,151 --> 00:13:30,448
<i>Mi chiami Margaret.</i>

197
00:13:38,917 --> 00:13:40,318
[chuckles]

198
00:13:40,454 --> 00:13:41,481
Hi.

199
00:13:44,950 --> 00:13:47,085
[metal clinking]

200
00:13:54,013 --> 00:13:56,415
[♪ soft suspenseful
music playing]

201
00:14:04,413 --> 00:14:05,948
Um... [gasps]

202
00:14:06,084 --> 00:14:07,452
What are you doing?

203
00:14:07,588 --> 00:14:08,912
Get off of me!

204
00:14:09,048 --> 00:14:10,250
[gasps]

205
00:14:11,546 --> 00:14:13,476
[breathing heavily]

206
00:14:13,612 --> 00:14:14,784
[footsteps approaching]

207
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:16,613
[Silva] Oh, there you are.

208
00:14:19,221 --> 00:14:22,217
Have you been
behaving yourself, Carlita?

209
00:14:24,982 --> 00:14:26,184
Carlita.

210
00:14:28,055 --> 00:14:30,645
Did you do that drawing
outside, Carlita?

211
00:14:30,781 --> 00:14:32,543
The one where
the girl's floating

212
00:14:32,678 --> 00:14:34,052
above the other girls?

213
00:14:36,283 --> 00:14:38,151
I thought it was very nice.

214
00:14:41,511 --> 00:14:43,514
[paper rustling]

215
00:14:48,445 --> 00:14:49,481
Thank you.

216
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:52,514
Come.

217
00:14:59,517 --> 00:15:00,576
Why is she kept alone
like that

218
00:15:00,712 --> 00:15:01,881
in the middle of the day?

219
00:15:02,016 --> 00:15:03,052
It's safer.

220
00:15:03,188 --> 00:15:06,184
She hurt another child
just yesterday.

221
00:15:08,052 --> 00:15:10,215
Luca will be your driver.

222
00:15:10,350 --> 00:15:12,311
Rome has become
a bit dangerous

223
00:15:12,446 --> 00:15:13,679
with the protests.

224
00:15:23,216 --> 00:15:26,283
[<i>♪ Our Love</i> by Percy Faith
playing on record player]

225
00:15:28,554 --> 00:15:29,778
[door opens]

226
00:15:31,445 --> 00:15:32,514
[suitcase thuds]

227
00:15:35,446 --> 00:15:36,448
[door closes]

228
00:15:44,411 --> 00:15:45,415
Hello?

229
00:16:17,485 --> 00:16:20,019
[♪ slow suspenseful
music playing]

230
00:16:26,149 --> 00:16:27,580
[music fades out]

231
00:16:40,346 --> 00:16:41,549
[exhales]

232
00:16:41,684 --> 00:16:44,252
By Your divine mercy,
rein in the power of evil.

233
00:16:44,388 --> 00:16:46,986
Build us into living stones
of a culture of life,

234
00:16:47,122 --> 00:16:49,045
who demonstrates
in both deed and word,

235
00:16:49,180 --> 00:16:51,186
the truth that every life,
no matter its conditions,

236
00:16:51,321 --> 00:16:52,777
- is precious and unrepeatable.
- [wind blowing]

237
00:16:52,913 --> 00:16:55,018
Lord, speak
to every human heart

238
00:16:55,154 --> 00:16:56,376
and fill it
with the conviction:

239
00:16:56,511 --> 00:16:57,685
I am wanted.

240
00:16:57,821 --> 00:16:59,247
I have a task in history.

241
00:16:59,383 --> 00:17:01,284
I am accepted, and I am loved.

242
00:17:01,420 --> 00:17:03,547
- It is good that I exist.
- [doorknob clicks]

243
00:17:10,188 --> 00:17:12,744
[♪ choral music
playing distantly]

244
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:14,148
[woman sighs]
Margaret's one of

245
00:17:14,284 --> 00:17:16,283
our worst-behaved children...

246
00:17:16,950 --> 00:17:19,110
[rattling]

247
00:17:19,246 --> 00:17:21,911
[woman 2 whispers] What if
she has another episode?

248
00:17:22,046 --> 00:17:24,052
[woman] Then you must
tie her to the bed.

249
00:17:25,150 --> 00:17:28,052
Here. Let me show you.

250
00:17:29,786 --> 00:17:31,283
[wind blowing]

251
00:17:43,185 --> 00:17:45,277
- [voice cries out]
- [gasps]

252
00:17:45,412 --> 00:17:46,584
[door shuts]

253
00:17:46,719 --> 00:17:48,085
[footsteps]

254
00:17:53,654 --> 00:17:54,646
[keys clatter]

255
00:17:56,687 --> 00:17:58,250
[breath shudders]

256
00:18:06,379 --> 00:18:08,385
- Hi.
- [gasps]

257
00:18:08,521 --> 00:18:09,752
<i>Mierda.</i>

258
00:18:09,887 --> 00:18:12,083
Ah, you must be Margaretta.

259
00:18:12,218 --> 00:18:13,283
- Yes.
- [chuckles softly]

260
00:18:13,418 --> 00:18:16,452
- I'm Luz. [smooches]
- Oh. [chuckles]

