[Margaret] Oh, no.

761
00:44:50,580 --> 00:44:51,880
No, no, no, don't. Don't!

762
00:44:52,015 --> 00:44:53,349
Don't!

763
00:44:53,484 --> 00:44:55,848
- [Margaret gasps]
- [girls screaming]

764
00:44:55,983 --> 00:44:56,947
[screaming]

765
00:44:57,082 --> 00:44:58,283
[both gasp]

766
00:44:58,851 --> 00:45:00,448
[shrieks]

767
00:45:03,379 --> 00:45:04,652
[screaming]

768
00:45:04,788 --> 00:45:06,915
[nun shouting in Italian]

769
00:45:07,050 --> 00:45:09,179
[girls screaming]

770
00:45:09,315 --> 00:45:12,349
- [panicked chatter]
- [♪ eerie operatic
music plays]

771
00:45:14,787 --> 00:45:16,547
[breathing shakily]

772
00:45:23,687 --> 00:45:24,679
[music fades out]

773
00:45:25,947 --> 00:45:28,283
[♪ slow suspenseful
music playing]

774
00:46:10,281 --> 00:46:12,919
- [voice 1] <i>Psst. Psst, psst.</i>
- [voice 2 speaks indistinctly]

775
00:46:13,055 --> 00:46:15,481
- [knock at door]
- [door unlocking]

776
00:46:18,017 --> 00:46:20,217
Margaret. Come in.

777
00:46:25,149 --> 00:46:27,250
[wind howling]

778
00:46:43,218 --> 00:46:45,547
Something happened, didn't it?

779
00:46:47,016 --> 00:46:49,151
Yes. Um...

780
00:46:49,286 --> 00:46:52,151
One of the sisters
took her own life.

781
00:46:55,913 --> 00:46:57,711
You mentioned
the name "Scianna."

782
00:46:57,847 --> 00:46:59,481
That's right.
[breathes heavily]

783
00:47:06,451 --> 00:47:08,415
I assume you know
these people.

784
00:47:09,954 --> 00:47:11,683
The priest is named Spiletto.

785
00:47:11,818 --> 00:47:13,184
He's a radical.

786
00:47:13,853 --> 00:47:15,244
Yes, I've seen him.

787
00:47:15,380 --> 00:47:16,382
Turn it over.

788
00:47:21,387 --> 00:47:23,443
[Margaret] The baby
in this photo is Carlita?

789
00:47:23,579 --> 00:47:25,053
[Brennan] I believe so.

790
00:47:25,188 --> 00:47:27,052
[Margaret] And this is why
she's in danger?

791
00:47:30,183 --> 00:47:31,619
I know these sisters.

792
00:47:31,754 --> 00:47:33,081
They're women of God.

793
00:47:33,217 --> 00:47:34,717
They belong to the Church.

794
00:47:34,853 --> 00:47:36,852
Listen to me, Margaret.

795
00:47:36,988 --> 00:47:40,250
The truth is
there are two Churches.

796
00:47:40,385 --> 00:47:42,249
The one that follows
the teachings of Christ,

797
00:47:42,385 --> 00:47:44,085
the one that you and I
are part of.

798
00:47:45,017 --> 00:47:46,185
And the other.

799
00:47:47,121 --> 00:47:49,080
The Church
that will turn a blind eye

800
00:47:49,216 --> 00:47:51,712
to torture, to rape.

801
00:47:51,847 --> 00:47:53,348
To commit murder
in the name of God.

802
00:47:53,484 --> 00:47:56,078
All in the name
of supreme power.

803
00:47:56,213 --> 00:47:59,019
What do you think that Church
is most frightened of?

804
00:48:00,478 --> 00:48:01,547
The Devil?

805
00:48:02,412 --> 00:48:03,976
Secularism.

806
00:48:04,945 --> 00:48:08,112
We are living
in unprecedented times.

807
00:48:08,247 --> 00:48:11,349
Look at what's been occurring
in your very own generation.

808
00:48:11,485 --> 00:48:14,014
A culture that is outspoken, rebelling.

809
00:48:14,150 --> 00:48:16,143
Sometimes violently.

810
00:48:16,279 --> 00:48:19,711
People are turning away
from the church in droves.

811
00:48:19,846 --> 00:48:22,543
And, Margaret,
you know as well as I do

812
00:48:22,678 --> 00:48:25,517
that belief is power.

813
00:48:25,652 --> 00:48:28,349
Now, how do you control people
who no longer believe

814
00:48:28,485 --> 00:48:31,144
in your stories
of fire and brimstone?

815
00:48:31,847 --> 00:48:34,085
People who do not
seem to fear?

816
00:48:35,284 --> 00:48:38,316
You create something to fear.

817
00:48:39,519 --> 00:48:43,080
This Church has maintained
power for generations.

818
00:48:43,216 --> 00:48:44,681
Thousands of years.

819
00:48:44,817 --> 00:48:47,377
And they will stop at nothing
to keep it that way.

820
00:48:47,513 --> 00:48:48,681
[breathing shakily]

821
00:48:48,817 --> 00:48:50,019
So,

822
00:48:51,218 --> 00:48:54,750
a small,
but very powerful group

823
00:48:54,886 --> 00:48:56,448
of priests and bishops,

824
00:48:57,478 --> 00:48:58,547
even higher,

825
00:48:59,983 --> 00:49:01,744
they decided

826
00:49:01,880 --> 00:49:04,085
something drastic
had to be done.

827
00:49:05,284 --> 00:49:07,449
These priests... [shuddering]

828
00:49:07,584 --> 00:49:09,916
...believe they can birth
the Antichrist

829
00:49:10,051 --> 00:49:11,448
and then control him.

830
00:49:12,550 --> 00:49:15,051
Allow him to bring
his dark forces

831
00:49:15,187 --> 00:49:16,877
to bear on the world
just enough

832
00:49:17,012 --> 00:49:19,076
to drive people
back to the Church.

833
00:49:19,512 --> 00:49:20,750
That's insane.

834
00:49:20,886 --> 00:49:22,513
Yes. Don't you see?

835
00:49:22,649 --> 00:49:25,752
If no one believes
such a thing can exist,

836
00:49:25,887 --> 00:49:28,085
who will stand in their way?

837
00:49:28,654 --> 00:49:31,052
[sighs] Uh...

838
00:49:31,188 --> 00:49:33,850
What does any of this
have to do with Carlita?

839
00:49:33,985 --> 00:49:35,879
I was excommunicated.

840
00:49:36,014 --> 00:49:38,215
My contacts within the Church
are very limited.

841
00:49:38,350 --> 00:49:40,878
That photo is all I have
to go on.

842
00:49:41,013 --> 00:49:45,383
But I believe the baby girl
in the picture

843
00:49:45,919 --> 00:49:47,651
is to be the mother.

844
00:49:47,787 --> 00:49:49,547
The mother of what?

845
00:49:55,512 --> 00:49:57,217
Of the Antichrist?

846
00:49:57,619 --> 00:49:58,646
Yes.

847
00:50:00,679 --> 00:50:02,153
Oh, my God. You're crazy.

848
00:50:02,288 --> 00:50:04,944
Look, if I am right,
Carlita would have been born

849
00:50:05,080 --> 00:50:07,516
on the sixth day
of the sixth month at 6 a.m.

850
00:50:07,652 --> 00:50:08,718
666.

851
00:50:08,854 --> 00:50:09,843
It's the mark of the Devil

852
00:50:09,979 --> 00:50:11,384
which she will have
on her body.

853
00:50:11,519 --> 00:50:13,911
I don't understand
why you're telling me this.

854
00:50:14,047 --> 00:50:15,650
They're keeping her files
at the orphanage.

855
00:50:15,785 --> 00:50:17,115
Locked away.

856
00:50:17,251 --> 00:50:19,249
I need you to get them to me.

857
00:50:19,385 --> 00:50:22,811
I need to know
how she was born.

858
00:50:22,946 --> 00:50:24,717
What do you mean,
how she was born?

859
00:50:24,853 --> 00:50:25,951
Listen to me, Margaret.

860
00:50:26,086 --> 00:50:27,746
There is a beast
they're mating.

861
00:50:27,881 --> 00:50:30,217
- A jackal. That's the father.
- [gasping]

862
00:50:30,352 --> 00:50:32,852
- I have to go now.
- No, no, Margaret.

863
00:50:32,988 --> 00:50:35,178
If Carlita is, in fact,
the mother,

864
00:50:35,313 --> 00:50:38,744
the evil inside her will do
whatever it takes to stop us.

865
00:50:38,880 --> 00:50:41,050
We must destroy it
at all costs.

866
00:50:41,185 --> 00:50:42,949
- Do you understand?
- No.

867
00:50:43,085 --> 00:50:45,476
Carlita is a little girl.

868
00:50:45,612 --> 00:50:46,812
And she is not pregnant.

869
00:50:46,947 --> 00:50:49,679
But we're not talking
about a human child!

870
00:50:50,579 --> 00:50:51,847
It's almost June 6th.

871
00:50:51,982 --> 00:50:54,411
Look, we haven't a lot of time
and I need your help.

872
00:50:54,546 --> 00:50:55,886
No, you need a doctor.

873
00:50:56,022 --> 00:50:58,085
I'm sorry
that I can't help you.

874
00:50:58,854 --> 00:51:00,415
Will you let go of my arm?

875
00:51:01,886 --> 00:51:03,415
[latches unlocking]

876
00:51:09,413 --> 00:51:12,118
- [♪ suspenseful music playing]
- [indistinct chatter]

877
00:51:30,413 --> 00:51:31,248
Oh. Margaret.

878
00:51:31,383 --> 00:51:33,185
- Hi.
- How are you feeling?

879
00:51:33,320 --> 00:51:36,217
Um, I need to talk to you
about Carlita.

880
00:51:38,914 --> 00:51:41,744
Do you know anything
about her history,

881
00:51:41,880 --> 00:51:45,085
or how she came
to the orphanage?

882
00:51:45,220 --> 00:51:49,319
Um, not off the top
of my head. Why?

883
00:51:49,455 --> 00:51:53,415
Do you know where I could find
that kind of information?

884
00:51:55,651 --> 00:51:59,481
I'm afraid this is not really
my area, you know?

885
00:52:17,913 --> 00:52:20,283
[man on radio
speaking Italian]

886
00:52:23,216 --> 00:52:25,250
[indistinct chatter]

887
00:52:27,880 --> 00:52:30,085
[radio chatter in Italian
continues]

888
00:52:44,684 --> 00:52:47,250
[♪ suspenseful music
continues playing]

889
00:52:58,784 --> 00:52:59,778
What?

890
00:53:01,185 --> 00:53:02,816
Why do you keep
staring at me?

891
00:53:02,952 --> 00:53:04,384
[margaret chuckles]

892
00:53:04,520 --> 00:53:05,514
I'm not.

893
00:53:14,282 --> 00:53:15,646
Will you come with me?

894
00:53:17,652 --> 00:53:18,646
Come on.

895
00:53:22,947 --> 00:53:25,019
I need to talk to you
about something.

896
00:53:25,721 --> 00:53:27,045
But before I do, I...

897
00:53:27,180 --> 00:53:30,349
I just want you to know
that you can trust me, okay?

898
00:53:31,784 --> 00:53:33,052
Okay.

899
00:53:33,685 --> 00:53:34,712
Um...

900
00:53:37,220 --> 00:53:40,712
Has anyone ever
done anything to you

901
00:53:41,745 --> 00:53:44,452
that might have scared you

902
00:53:44,588 --> 00:53:46,151
or upset you?

903
00:53:50,982 --> 00:53:52,184
Uh...

904
00:53:52,687 --> 00:53:53,745
I don't know.

905
00:53:55,513 --> 00:53:56,745
What don't you know?

906
00:53:59,987 --> 00:54:02,547
[inhales]
Sometimes I get this...

907
00:54:03,786 --> 00:54:05,349
bad feelings.

908
00:54:08,520 --> 00:54:09,548
I see...

909
00:54:10,418 --> 00:54:12,316
I see things.
[breath trembling]

910
00:54:13,583 --> 00:54:18,184
And I can't tell
if they're real or not.

911
00:54:20,050 --> 00:54:21,547
Listen to me.

912
00:54:22,886 --> 00:54:24,976
When I was younger,

913
00:54:25,745 --> 00:54:27,514
I... I used to have these

914
00:54:28,413 --> 00:54:31,016
horrible visions.

915
00:54:31,151 --> 00:54:33,986
They were so terrible that I

916
00:54:34,121 --> 00:54:37,085
convinced myself
that they were real.

917
00:54:38,253 --> 00:54:42,613
But I learned
that those thoughts,

918
00:54:43,579 --> 00:54:46,043
they were just lies.

919
00:54:46,179 --> 00:54:48,916
Just tricks that my brain
was playing on me

920
00:54:49,052 --> 00:54:51,415
because I was so unhappy.

921
00:54:52,116 --> 00:54:53,348
This isn't a lie.

922
00:54:53,484 --> 00:54:55,382
How can you know that
for certain?

923
00:54:59,246 --> 00:55:00,218
Carlita.

924
00:55:00,587 --> 00:55:01,646
I'm sorry.

925
00:55:06,345 --> 00:55:07,349
Carlita.

926
00:55:11,854 --> 00:55:14,881
[sighs] Carlita. I'm sorry.

927
00:55:15,016 --> 00:55:17,118
[woman giggling]

928
00:55:27,821 --> 00:55:29,448
[♪ cryptic music plays]

929
00:55:35,982 --> 00:55:36,980
[gasps]

930
00:55:37,116 --> 00:55:38,948
There you are.

931
00:55:39,084 --> 00:55:40,584
A riot's broken out.

932
00:55:40,719 --> 00:55:41,951
We must go.

933
00:55:42,086 --> 00:55:44,151
[guard] <i>Deve andare adesso!</i>

934
00:55:46,085 --> 00:55:47,481
<i>Deve andare adesso!</i>

935
00:55:49,885 --> 00:55:51,651
[people clamoring]

936
00:55:51,787 --> 00:55:53,515
[protestors yelling]

937
00:55:53,650 --> 00:55:55,677
[Margaret] Listen.
It's all right, girls.

938
00:55:55,812 --> 00:55:57,483
It's okay.
Stay close to me, okay?

939
00:55:57,619 --> 00:55:58,613
Oh.

940
00:56:01,847 --> 00:56:04,052
[protestors chanting
indistinctly]

941
00:56:09,787 --> 00:56:11,448
Stay close to me, okay?

942
00:56:13,752 --> 00:56:15,283
[gasping]

943
00:56:16,952 --> 00:56:18,450
[protestors clamoring]

944
00:56:18,586 --> 00:56:20,184
Carlita!

945
00:56:22,578 --> 00:56:23,712
[molotov shatters]

946
00:56:26,817 --> 00:56:28,019
Carlita!

947
00:56:31,478 --> 00:56:32,615
[explosion]

948
00:56:32,751 --> 00:56:33,778
[gasps]

949
00:56:37,612 --> 00:56:39,085
[Margaret grunting]

950
00:56:42,919 --> 00:56:44,382
[continues grunting]

951
00:56:48,785 --> 00:56:49,852
[Margaret gasps]

952
00:56:49,987 --> 00:56:52,184
[♪ sinister music playing]

953
00:56:54,115 --> 00:56:56,316
[screaming]

954
00:56:57,881 --> 00:57:00,284
- [shout echoes]
- [ambient noises fade]

955
00:57:00,419 --> 00:57:03,085
[♪ surreal choral
music playing]

956
00:57:24,318 --> 00:57:26,712
[♪ surreal music intensifies]

957
00:57:33,853 --> 00:57:35,415
[Silva] <i>Silenzio.</i>

958
00:57:37,413 --> 00:57:39,019
<i>Silenzio.</i>

959
00:57:39,819 --> 00:57:41,052
[music fades out]

960
00:57:41,820 --> 00:57:45,077
<i>Silenzio, ragazze.</i>

961
00:57:45,212 --> 00:57:48,613
[on PA] <i>Padre nostro,
che sei nei cieli,</i>

962
00:57:49,747 --> 00:57:54,119
<i>sia santificato
il tuo nome,</i>

963
00:57:54,255 --> 00:57:56,511
<i>venga il tuo regno...</i>
[voice fading out]

964
00:57:56,646 --> 00:57:58,019
[nun whispering] Margaretta.

965
00:58:03,180 --> 00:58:06,514
Sister Silva would like
to see you in her office.

966
00:58:13,886 --> 00:58:15,415
Please take a seat.

967
00:58:19,884 --> 00:58:21,085
[clears throat]

968
00:58:22,445 --> 00:58:23,514
Margaret...

969
00:58:25,451 --> 00:58:28,612
Part of my job here
is to look out

970
00:58:28,747 --> 00:58:30,586
for the well-being
of all those

971
00:58:30,721 --> 00:58:33,216
who are under my care.

972
00:58:33,352 --> 00:58:36,883
I'm sure this will come
as no surprise,

973
00:58:37,019 --> 00:58:39,679
but I've become concerned.

974
00:58:41,688 --> 00:58:43,316
I'm fine. [chuckles]

975
00:58:47,079 --> 00:58:49,745
Perhaps I should have
put it this way.

976
00:58:50,578 --> 00:58:52,580
We are concerned.

977
00:58:53,647 --> 00:58:56,382
Myself and Cardinal Lawrence.

978
00:58:58,313 --> 00:59:01,282
We think it might be time
for you to take a step back.

979
00:59:01,418 --> 00:59:03,584
And perhaps
we postpone your vows.

980
00:59:03,720 --> 00:59:05,748
What? No. Why?

981
00:59:05,884 --> 00:59:09,747
We're also concerned about
your attachment to Carlita.

982
00:59:09,883 --> 00:59:11,217
Carlita?

983
00:59:12,187 --> 00:59:13,886
- But...
- Cardinal Lawrence told me

984
00:59:14,022 --> 00:59:16,080
about your troubles
growing up.

985
00:59:16,216 --> 00:59:18,319
Your hallucinations.

986
00:59:18,455 --> 00:59:23,476
Perhaps being around Carlita
is not what's right for you.

987
00:59:23,612 --> 00:59:24,818
[voices whispering]

988
00:59:24,954 --> 00:59:28,315
[Silva] Carlita is disturbed.

989
00:59:28,451 --> 00:59:31,443
And her illness
must not infect us

990
00:59:31,578 --> 00:59:33,448
as her caretakers.

991
00:59:34,051 --> 00:59:36,476
And clearly, it has.

992
00:59:36,611 --> 00:59:37,712
[whispering stops]

993
00:59:38,751 --> 00:59:39,778
Wait.

994
00:59:43,719 --> 00:59:45,215
I'm not ill.

995
00:59:45,351 --> 00:59:48,585
I understand
how hard you had to work

996
00:59:48,721 --> 00:59:50,416
to get to where you are.

997
00:59:50,551 --> 00:59:53,250
It would be a shame
to give it all up now.

998
00:59:53,386 --> 00:59:56,015
I am the only one
who cares about her.

999
00:59:56,150 --> 00:59:57,218
You don't let her play

1000
00:59:57,353 --> 00:59:58,582
- with the other girls.
- I've told you...

1001
00:59:58,718 --> 01:00:00,048
- You keep her in the bad room.
- ...we're only doing

1002
01:00:00,183 --> 01:00:01,181
what's right for her.

1003
01:00:01,317 --> 01:00:02,745
The girl is sick in the head.

1004
01:00:02,881 --> 01:00:05,745
- Because of you!
- [nuns gasp, whisper]

1005
01:00:09,578 --> 01:00:11,143
[breathes shakily]

1006
01:00:12,013 --> 01:00:16,247
If there was any doubt
in our decision,

1007
01:00:16,382 --> 01:00:18,378
you've all but confirmed it.

1008
01:00:18,513 --> 01:00:20,184
You're clearly unwell.

1009
01:00:21,984 --> 01:00:23,779
And, Margaret,

1010
01:00:23,914 --> 01:00:27,043
you will keep your distance
from Carlita.

1011
01:00:27,746 --> 01:00:30,743
Or there will be consequences.

1012
01:00:30,879 --> 01:00:33,217
[♪ discordant music playing]

1013
01:00:43,754 --> 01:00:45,217
Stop the car, Luca.

1014
01:00:48,847 --> 01:00:49,981
I can just walk home
from here, okay?

1015
01:00:50,117 --> 01:00:51,580
You don't have to wait.

1016
01:00:53,246 --> 01:00:54,250
Paolo.

1017
01:00:54,619 --> 01:00:55,613
Paolo!

1018
01:00:56,553 --> 01:00:57,547
Paolo!

1019
01:01:00,952 --> 01:01:02,053
[Paolo] No, no, no.

1020
01:01:02,188 --> 01:01:03,679
<i>Lasciami stare,
ti pego, ti prego.</i>

1021
01:01:05,784 --> 01:01:06,950
